1. `h₁ : False`: Since `hA : A.isKnave`, then `A.isKnave ∨ B.isKnave` is true, but `this : ¬(A.isKnave ∨ B.isKnave)` says it is false. This is a contradiction, so we get `False`.
2. `h₂ : A.isKnight ∧ B.isKnave`: From `False`, we can derive any conclusion, including `A.isKnight ∧ B.isKnave`.

